RABIES - INDONESIA (EAST NUSA TENGGARA)
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri, 29 Sep 2006 00:22:15 +0200
From: Thomas Schmidt <tho-schmidt@web.de>
Source: Kupang Post, 23 Sep 2006 [edited]
<http://www.indomedia.com/poskup/2006/09/23/edisi23/floresa.htm>

Over the last week, 19 citizens in 3 villages in the Palue
Subdistrict, Sikka, were bitten by dogs suspecting of having rabies.
Two heads of the dogs were sent to Maumere to be checked further,
while the bite casualties were treated in the Palue Community Health Centre.
The Kupang Post in Maumere on Thu 21 Sep mentioned that, of the 19
bitten by possible rabid dogs, 5 came from the Reruwairere Village, 4
from Maluriwu and 11 from the Nitunglea Village [this gives a total
of 20; clearly an error somewhere]. "This report was given by the
Palue Sub-district Head to the Sikka Regional Government," said a
citizen from Palue.
Separately, the Representative of the Regent Sikka, Drs. Yoseph Ansar
Rera, confirmed the information on Thu 21 Sep. According to Wabup
Ansar Rera, the Sub-district Head of Palue, he was just handed the
report concerning the rabies dog bites last Tuesday (19 Sep). "After
I received the report from the sub-district head, bite casualties
from the Reruwairere Village and the Maluriwu Village were
immediately handled by a doctor from Puskesmas Palue. Casualties
from the village of Nitunglea were treated the next day. I did not
know whether the bites happened almost simultaneously or not, but I
just received his report on Tuesday (19 Sep)," explained Wabup Ansar Rera.
Apart from handling these cases, the Sikka Regional Government also
dispatched 6 officials of the ministry of agriculture to perform
vaccinations in Palue. "If the report had been handed in earlier,
then the officials would have been dispatched earlier," [an official?] said.
---
